  "name": "adam",
  "description": "Deterministic AI research kernel for agglutinative languages. Applied demonstrator of Qazaq IR — a deterministic alternative to probabilistic large language models, built on Kazakh agglutinative morphology. Three guarantees: predictability (every claim traceable to a curated source), cheapness (single binary, 0% GPU, ~21 ms p50 latency, ~300 MB RSS), safety (architectural impossibility of hallucination). Generalises across ~30 catalogued agglutinative languages.",
